body:
I tried this code ([playground]):

```rust
#![feature(try_trait_v2)]

use std::ops::{Try, FromResidual, ControlFlow};

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, PartialOrd, Eq, Ord, Hash)]
#[repr(u8)]
enum Bool {
    False = 0,
    True = 1,
}

use Bool::{False, True};

impl Try for Bool {
    type Output = Self;
    type Residual = Self;
    
    fn from_output(output: Self) -> Self {
        output
    }
    
    fn branch(self) -> ControlFlow<Self, Self> {
        match self {
            False => ControlFlow::Break(self),
            True => ControlFlow::Continue(self),
        }
    }
}

impl FromResidual<Self> for Bool {
    fn from_residual(residual: Self) -> Self {
        residual
    }
}

impl<T> FromResidual<Bool> for Option<T> {
    fn from_residual(residual: Bool) -> Self {
        None
    }
}
```

[playground]: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=5f1c551c59778be5fa911dd8015066ba

I expected to see the code to compile.

Instead this failed to compile with the following error:

```
Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)
error[[E0119]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/error-index.html#E0119): conflicting implementations of trait `std::ops::FromResidual<Bool>` for type `std::option::Option<_>`
  --> src/lib.rs:36:1
   |
36 | impl<T> FromResidual<Bool> for Option<T> {
   | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
   |
   = note: conflicting implementation in crate `core`:
           - impl<T> FromResidual for Option<T>;

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0119`.
error: could not compile `playground` due to previous error
```

I don’t think that `FromResidual<Bool> for Option<T>` conflicts with `FromResidual for Option<T>`, since the latter is actually `FromResidual<<Option<T> as Try>::Residual> for Option<T>`, which is `FromResidual<Option<Infallible>> for Option<T>`, and `Bool` is always distinct from `Option<T>`.

### Meta

Reproduces on playground  (1.66.0-nightly (2022-10-05 c97d02cdb5ca5f5e9eff))

Possible duplicate of #94940, possibly related to #98829
